True Drinks Holdings, Inc. Key Developments

True Drinks Holdings, Inc. Reports Revenue Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 12 17
True Drinks Holdings, Inc. reported revenue results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. Revenue for the second quarter totaled approximately $1.95 million, representing a 27% increase compared to the Company's first-quarter sales. 

The Company had record first-half revenues for the six months ended June 30, 2017 of nearly $3.5 million, an increase of 225% over the six months ended June 30, 2016. The strong growth was primarily the result of AquaBall's continued sales gains in the children's beverage category, driven by enhanced brand awareness among consumers looking to purchase a healthy alternative to sugary beverages.


True Drinks Holdings, Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
May 16 17
True Drinks Holdings, Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net sales were $1,529,752 against $583,298 a year ago. Operating loss was $2,445,300 against $2,287,376 a year ago. Net loss attributable to common shareholders was $334,918 or $0.00 basic and diluted loss per share against $1,245,774 or $0.01 basic and diluted loss per share a year ago. Net cash used in operating activities was $3,743,120 against $626,222 a year ago.


True Drinks Holdings, Inc. Announces Management Changes
Apr 18 17
True Drinks Holdings, Inc. announced the appointment of James J. Greco as CEO. Mr. Greco had previously been recruited directly by former CEO, Kevin Sherman and appointed as a Director of True Drinks on February 6, 2017. He will now take over day-to-day operations as the company's CEO. Kevin Sherman will retain the role of President. Mr. Greco currently serves as President and Chief Executive Officer of Pilgrim Holdings, LLC, a position he has held since October 2001. Mr. Greco previously served as Chief Operating Officer of Newk's Franchise Company, LLC from July 2014 until October 2016, as well as President from January 2016 until October 2016.


